\begin_layout Standard
Central to many value chain studies is the question of how rents are distributed over different value chain actors.
 A convenient way to illustrate this is by price spread plots,
 that plot prices received by the actor upstream (eg the farmer) against prices received by the actor downstream (eg the trader).
 One can then plot a 45 degree line,
